        <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto:wght@300&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

        <link rel="stylesheet" href="./css/style.css"></link>
    </head>
    <body>
        <h1>Bassdrive Archive Randomizer</h1>
        <p>
            This began as a labour of love in December of 2020 while I was 
            in Covid 19 lockdown. I wanted to write a micro-service in Go and I had stumbled upon <a href="http://bassdrive.com" target="_blank">Bassdrive's</a>
            very generous archive of Drum and Bass mixes going back over a decade. So I built a database of all the archive files 
            and a web API which serves them up on demand. I like to be surprised so this page allows you to randomize a new mix whenever
            you want simply by refreshing it. 
        </p>
        <p>
            Feel free to follow me on <a href="http://twitter.com/realpunkscience" target="_blank">Twitter</a> 
        </p>
        <h2>{{.Name}}</h2> 
        <p><audio controls><source src="{{.URL}}" type="audio/mpeg"></audio></p>
    </body>
</html>
